#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn15.20"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn15.20:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 15 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 15 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn15.20:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga "
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn15.20:0.3"
msgid "20. Vepullapabbatasutta "
msgstr "20. Mount Vepulla "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn15.20:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "sn15.20:1.3"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn15.20:1.4"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.191, sc2
msgctxt "sn15.20:2.1"
msgid "“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:2.2"
msgid "Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ. "
msgstr "No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:2.3"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa vepullassa pabbatassa ‘pācīnavaṃso’tveva samaññā udapādi. "
msgstr "Once upon a time, mendicants, this Mount Vepulla was known as Pācīnavaṃsa. "

# NOTE: BB has “these people”, but there is no imesam. Tivara was the name of people generally, not just those in the region.
msgctxt "sn15.20:2.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena manussānaṃ ‘tivarā’tveva samaññā udapādi. "
msgstr "And at that time people were known as Tivaras. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:2.5"
msgid "Tivarānaṃ, bhikkhave, manussānaṃ cattārīsa vassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "The lifespan of the Tivaras was 40,000 years. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:2.6"
msgid "Tivarā, bhikkhave, manussā pācīnavaṃsaṃ pabbataṃ catūhena ārohanti, catūhena orohanti. "
msgstr "It took them four days to climb Mount Vepulla, and four days to descend. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:2.7"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena kakusandho bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno hoti. "
msgstr "At that time Kakusandha, the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha arose in the world. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:2.8"
msgid "Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa vidhurasañjīvaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "Kakusandha had a fine pair of chief disciples named Vidhura and Sañjīva. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:2.9"
msgid "Passatha, bhikkhave, sā cevimassa pabbatassa samaññā antarahitā, te ca manussā kālaṅkatā, so ca bhagavā parinibbuto. "
msgstr "See, mendicants! This mountain’s name has vanished, those people have passed away, and that Buddha has become fully extinguished. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:2.10"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā; "
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions, "

msgctxt "sn15.20:2.11"
msgid "evaṃ addhuvā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā; "
msgstr "so unstable are conditions, "

msgctxt "sn15.20:2.12"
msgid "evaṃ anassāsikā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā. "
msgstr "so unreliable are conditions. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:2.13"
msgid "Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ, alaṃ virajjituṃ, alaṃ vimuccituṃ. "
msgstr "This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn15.20:3.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa vepullassa pabbatassa ‘vaṅkako’tveva samaññā udapādi. "
msgstr "Once upon a time this Mount Vepulla was known as Vaṅkaka. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:3.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena manussānaṃ ‘rohitassā’tveva samaññā udapādi. "
msgstr "And at that time people were known as Rohitassas. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:3.3"
msgid "Rohitassānaṃ, bhikkhave, manussānaṃ tiṃsavassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "The lifespan of the Rohitassas was 30,000 years. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:3.4"
msgid "Rohitassā, bhikkhave, manussā vaṅkakaṃ pabbataṃ tīhena ārohanti, tīhena orohanti. "
msgstr "It took them three days to climb Mount Vepulla, and three days to descend. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:3.5"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena koṇāgamano bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno hoti. "
msgstr "At that time Koṇāgamana, the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha arose in the world. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:3.6"
msgid "Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bhiyyosuttaraṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "Koṇāgamana had a fine pair of chief disciples named Bhiyyosa and Uttara. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:3.7"
msgid "Passatha, bhikkhave, sā cevimassa pabbatassa samaññā antarahitā, te ca manussā kālaṅkatā, so ca bhagavā parinibbuto. "
msgstr "See, mendicants! This mountain’s name has vanished, those people have passed away, and that Buddha has become fully extinguished. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:3.8"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā … pe … "
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions … "

msgctxt "sn15.20:3.9"
msgid "alaṃ vimuccituṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: supasso’tveva → suphasso tveva (bj)
msgctxt "sn15.20:4.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa vepullassa pabbatassa ‘supasso’tveva samaññā udapādi. "
msgstr "Once upon a time this Mount Vepulla was known as Supassa. "

#. VAR: suppiyā’tveva → appiyā tveva (si)
msgctxt "sn15.20:4.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena manussānaṃ ‘suppiyā’tveva samaññā udapādi. "
msgstr "And at that time people were known as Suppiyas. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:4.3"
msgid "Suppiyānaṃ, bhikkhave, manussānaṃ vīsativassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "The lifespan of the Suppiyas was 20,000 years. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:4.4"
msgid "Suppiyā, bhikkhave, manussā supassaṃ pabbataṃ dvīhena ārohanti, dvīhena orohanti. "
msgstr "It took them two days to climb Mount Vepulla, and two days to descend. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:4.5"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno hoti. "
msgstr "At that time Kassapa, the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha arose in the world. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:4.6"
msgid "Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tissabhāradvājaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "Kassapa had a fine pair of chief disciples named Tissa and Bhāradvāja. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:4.7"
msgid "Passatha, bhikkhave, sā cevimassa pabbatassa samaññā antarahitā, te ca manussā kālaṅkatā, so ca bhagavā parinibbuto. "
msgstr "See, mendicants! This mountain’s name has vanished, those people have passed away, and that Buddha has become fully extinguished. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:4.8"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā; "
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions … "

msgctxt "sn15.20:4.9"
msgid "evaṃ addhuvā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn15.20:4.10"
msgid "alaṃ vimuccituṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.193, sc5
msgctxt "sn15.20:5.1"
msgid "Etarahi kho pana, bhikkhave, imassa vepullassa pabbatassa ‘vepullo’tveva samaññā udapādi. "
msgstr "These days this Mount Vepulla is known as Vepulla. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:5.2"
msgid "Etarahi kho pana, bhikkhave, imesaṃ manussānaṃ ‘māgadhakā’tveva samaññā udapādi. "
msgstr "And these people are known as Magadhans. "

#. VAR: lahukaṃ → lahusaṃ (si)
msgctxt "sn15.20:5.3"
msgid "Māgadhakānaṃ, bhikkhave, manussānaṃ appakaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ parittaṃ lahukaṃ; "
msgstr "The lifespan of the Magadhans is short, brief, and fleeting. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:5.4"
msgid "yo ciraṃ jīvati so vassasataṃ appaṃ vā bhiyyo. "
msgstr "A long life is a hundred years or a little more. "

# NOTE: Note the arthasastra counts 15 muhurtas per day, and 15 per night. So “hour” is not too bad.
msgctxt "sn15.20:5.5"
msgid "Māgadhakā, bhikkhave, manussā vepullaṃ pabbataṃ muhuttena ārohanti muhuttena orohanti. "
msgstr "It takes the Magadhans an hour to climb Mount Vepulla, and an hour to descend. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:5.6"
msgid "Etarahi kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno. "
msgstr "And now I am the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha who has arisen in the world. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:5.7"
msgid "Mayhaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, sāriputtamoggallānaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ. "
msgstr "I have a fine pair of chief disciples named Sāriputta and Moggallāna. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:5.8"
msgid "Bhavissati, bhikkhave, so samayo yā ayañcevimassa pabbatassa samaññā antaradhāyissati, ime ca manussā kālaṃ karissanti, ahañca parinibbāyissāmi. "
msgstr "There will come a time when this mountain’s name will disappear, those people will die, and I will be fully extinguished. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:5.9"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā; "
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions, "

msgctxt "sn15.20:5.10"
msgid "evaṃ addhuvā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā; "
msgstr "so unstable are conditions, "

msgctxt "sn15.20:5.11"
msgid "evaṃ anassāsikā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā. "
msgstr "so unreliable are conditions. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:5.12"
msgid "Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ, alaṃ virajjituṃ, alaṃ vimuccitun”ti. "
msgstr "This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn15.20:6.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn15.20:6.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn15.20:7.1"
msgid "“Pācīnavaṃso tivarānaṃ, "
msgstr "“For the Tivaras it was Pācīnavaṃsa, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn15.20:7.2"
msgid "rohitassāna vaṅkako; "
msgstr "for the Rohitassa, Vaṅkaka, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn15.20:7.3"
msgid "Suppiyānaṃ supassoti, "
msgstr "Supassa for the Suppiyas, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn15.20:7.4"
msgid "māgadhānañca vepullo. "
msgstr "and Vepulla for the Magadhans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn15.20:8.1"
msgid "Aniccā vata saṅkhārā, "
msgstr "Oh! Conditions are impermanent, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn15.20:8.2"
msgid "uppādavayadhammino; "
msgstr "their nature is to rise and fall; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn15.20:8.3"
msgid "Uppajjitvā nirujjhanti, "
msgstr "having arisen, they cease; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn15.20:8.4"
msgid "tesaṃ vūpasamo sukho”ti. "
msgstr "their stilling is true bliss.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn15.20:8.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn15.20:8.6"
msgid "Dutiyo vaggo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn15.20:9.1"
msgid "Duggataṃ sukhitañceva, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn15.20:9.2"
msgid "tiṃsa mātāpitena ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn15.20:9.3"
msgid "Bhātā bhaginī putto ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn15.20:9.4"
msgid "dhītā vepullapabbataṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn15.20:9.5"
msgid "Anamataggasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on the unknown beginning are complete."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
